I"[<p>Two commone ways to index the <strong>loop variable</strong> in <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">for</code> loops are to use the form <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">for(variable in collection)</code> to pull the elements (“variable”) from a vector (“collection”) one at at time, or to use the form <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">for(i in 1:length(collection))</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">for(i in seq_along(collection))</code> to instead pull each index (i.e. location) in a vector one at a time.</p>
